Philia is a Greek word meaning love.

Philia refers to brotherly love, including friendship and affection.  This contrasts to the Greek terms [[Eros]], or sexual/romantic love, and [[Agape]], or detached, spiritual love.

The word also acts as a root in many English words.
* [[Bibliophilia]]   is the love of books.
* [[Bibliophile]]    is a lover of books.
* [[Logophilia]]     is the love of words.
* [[Logophile]]      is a lover of words.
* [[Hydrophilia]]    is the love of water.
* [[Hydrophile]]     is a lover of water and aquatic activities.
